column1: #Text=[0158] A solution of Example 22B (339 mg, 1.0 mmol) in a mixture of THF (5 mL) and water (3 mL) was treated with LiOH.H.sub.2O (84 mg, 2.0 mmol) in water (3 mL).
#Text=Methanol was added until a transparent solution formed (1 mL).
#Text=C. overnight and the organic solvents were removed under vacuum.
#Text=The residual aqueous solution was acidified with 2 N HCl to pH 2 and was partitioned between ethyl acetate and water.
#Text=The organic phase was washed with water, dried (MgSO.sub.4), filtered and concentrated to give Example 22C (310 mg, 88% yield).
